page.title: 01Risby to Cavenham
page.content: The block under review consists largely f arable farmland,interspersed quite plentifully with woodland.The general topography is that it is at its highest point at the Water Tower on the Risby - Cavenham road whence it falls gently to a small valley where a mostly seasonal stream flows North to the River Lark. The Parish boundary between Risby and Cavenham follows the general line of this little stream in the south of the block but leaves it to skirt an area known as Black Ditches.It rejoins the stream via the Icknield Way and largely follows the stream to its confluence with the River Lark.
